**Root cause:** `src/services/example.ts:42` — null check missing before accessing `.id` property  
**Logic drift:** The function assumed the user object was always populated, but unauthenticated requests could reach this path via a misconfigured middleware.

### Triple-Test Contract
| Scenario | Layer | Reasoning |
|---|---|---|
| ✅ Positive | Unit | Verifies authenticated requests return correct result |
| ❌ Negative | Unit | Verifies unauthenticated request throws expected error, not crashes |
| ⚠️ Edge | API | Verifies expired token is handled the same as no token |

### Resolution
Fixed null check in `src/services/example.ts`. All three tests implemented and passing.

